               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita of Takla Haymanot” (fols. 2ra-107ra)&#xD;
                     II) Maṣḥafa fǝlsätu la-ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot “Book of the Translation of ʾabuna
                     Takla Haymanot” (fols. 107va-114vb)&#xD; III) Taʾāmra Takla Hāymānot “Miracles
                     of ʾabuna Takla Haymanot”: 25 miracles (fols. 115ra-131rb)&#xD; &#xD;
                     Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The text of the Vita represents the later of the two sub-types of the
                        Dabra Libānos recension (close to the text published by E.A.W. BUDGE (ed.,
                        tr.), The Life and Miracles of Takla Hâymânôt in the Version of Dabra
                        Lîbânôs..., London, 1906; cp. also the Miracles).</note>
                     <note>Quire XVII apparently constitutes a separate production unit (<locus target="#13">13</locus>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ES0ra131">0ra-131</ref>rb; Miracle of the
                        resurrection of Bäṣalota Masqal is usually a story included in the
                        Vita).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
